About this item

  • A digital controller designed to equip outlet devices with smart controls for HVAC or growing applications.
  • Powers up to two outlet devices on or off and provides each with independent programming.
  • Programs include temperature, humidity, & VPD triggers, timers, cycles, scheduling, and custom buffers.
  • Pair with our app via Bluetooth or WiFi to unlock advance programs, set notifications, and view climate data.
  • Two outlets collectively support up to 1100W to control plugged-in devices together or independently.

Product Description

CONTROLLER 79 PRO

Dual Outlet Control

Monitor and control up two smart outlet devices. Set independent programming for your equipment based on separate climates and automations to ensure ideal growing conditions.

Advance Automations Made Easy

  1. Advance Programming


    Create automation for your devices to systematically manage your grow tent environment. Set customizable alerts that can trigger to almost any event.

  2. Greater Environmental Insight


    Interactive graph intuitively displays temperature, humidity, and VPD data. Input target figures to help your grow tent approach and maintain your ideal environment.

  3. Active Monitoring


    Stay on top of what's happening in your grow space using alerts and notifications so you can quickly counteract any environmental spikes.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

5 out of 5 stars
Amazing!
The "AC Infinity Controller 75 PRO, WiFi Outlet Controller" has so many different settings I'm not even sure where to start. It's great quality which is to be expected from AC Infinity! The app is easy to use as well as the physical controls. I currently have it set up for a heat mat and a humidifier and now that the weather is starting to get colder it's been a lifesaver for seed starting. You can put the probe directly into the soil to control the temperature of the soil instead of just the room and have the heat mat turn on according to the temperature you set in the app. You can have the humidifier turn on when the humidity reaches as certain level you set as well. The options are endless depending on what devices you set up. Seed starting and taking care of my more difficult plants has been made much easier with with this controller. Overall, I highly recommend this!

  • Geoff
    4.0 out of 5 stars Really cool outlet controller. Only two outlets/programs but very versatile
    Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2024
    Style: DesktopAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
    Pretty impressive. Most of AC Infinity's products are. Easy to set up, easy to use, and so far very reliable. Excellent quality item.
    AC Infinity has a lot of different offerings for controlling climate in grow tents and greenhouses. The benefit/shortcoming here is that there are only two outlets. Those outlets can run anything AC powered (up to 1100w) from any manufacturer, but the downside here is that you can only run 2 things (or only two programs). If you want to control a heater, a fan, a humidifier, and lights, or multiples of any of these or anything else, AC Infinity does have controllers for that. Just not this one. What it does though, it does very well. In my case, I will probably use this to control temperature and humidity in a grow tent next season. If I even need lighting control (not sure yet, the tent will most likely be inside my greenhouse), that's easy enough to just set up on a simple timer. It's great that this controller does offer SO much versatility though, and it will control devices on a timer as well as based on temperature and humidity. As I think others have mentioned, this could be used for things other than growing applications as well, controlling HVAC or any other temperature/humidity related items. The 1100w capacity is quite a bit of power, but not enough for larger heaters or a combination of high current devices. Still respectable for a device like this, but if you are running anything drawing more power, you need a different controller! I'm honestly not a fan of app controlled devices for the most part, but here it works great and really adds to the capabilities.

  • Jules
    5.0 out of 5 stars Easy Set-Up, Safety Features for Peace of Mind
    Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2024
    Style: DesktopAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
    Ive been a longtime fan of AC Infinity for greenhouse supplies, and theyve done it again. The smart outlet was a breeze to set-up, and it came with wall mount supplies to hang up the controller and probe. The user manual is brief but thorough, and some instructions included pictures to better show each step. The outlet can be programmed either manually on the LCD screen or via the AC Infinity app. The included probe gives an accurate reading of the temperature and humidity. (Im not sure how to verify VPD.)

    The app is available on both Google Play and App Store. You need to register an account to use the app, but it only asks for your name, email address, and to choose a password. The app is very easy to use/navigate, runs quickly, and hasnt lagged or crashed on me since I started using it (1.5 years). You can export your climate data, label which device is plugged into either outlet, and label the controller itself. Its also very easy to share the device (give another person access to the controller via the app); They just need to have an AC Infinity account before you send them an invite.

    I especially appreciate the safety features. The outlet also acts as a surge protector, which I wasnt expecting at all. The app will notify you IMMEDIATELY if the controller shuts off and needs to be reset. Theres also the option to set an alarm/alert on the app to notify you when the temperature, humidity, or VPD is out of range; and/or when your programmed settings are triggered. You can set the alarm to go off once with a notification, or to continuously alert you until you shut it off. The app can also run multiple alarms and/or automations simultaneously, as long as they dont conflict with one another. This makes me feel much better about running a heater in the greenhouse through the night since I know I wont be able to sleep through a continuous alarm, in the event that something goes terribly wrong.

    Im always impressed with the quality and thoughtfulness of AC Infinitys products, and the smart outlet is no exception. It can automate and monitor several processes - such as running grow lights, humidifiers, AC units, dehumidifiers, heaters, fans, seedling mats, etc. Its especially great if you love to constantly check in on your plants, want to maintain a constant environment for your plants, need to control your devices remotely, love collecting data, or just want to have one less responsibility on your plate. There's no competition: Compared to all the other tech I've used to keep my plants happy, this smart controller from AC Infinity blows everything else out of the water.
